subSubSection.paragraph:
Skeleton:
In cross section is observed a dense central axial condensation which forms a reticulated skeleton from which radiates to the surface an extra axial plumoreticulated skeleton (
Fig. 4A
). The extra axial skeleton is interconnected by scattered spicules or fibers in a reticulated pattern (
Fig. 4B
). Extra axial megascleres usually protrude through the surface where sometimes they form fan-shaped spicule brushes, whose tips also project beyond the surface (
Fig. 4D,E
).
